Refresh fotingo-managed pull request sections for the current branch using marker-delimited ownership in the PR body.

Supported sections: summary, description, fixed-issues, changes.

Usage:
  fotingo review sync [flags]

Flags:
  -a, --assignee strings              Assignees to add to the pull request (repeatable)
  -h, --help                          help for sync
      --ready-for-review              Move the existing draft pull request to ready for review
      --remove-assignee strings       Assignees to remove from the pull request (repeatable)
      --remove-reviewers strings      Review requests to remove from the pull request (users or teams, repeatable)
  -r, --reviewers strings             Reviewers to request on the pull request (users or teams, repeatable)
      --section strings               Sync only the specified fotingo-managed section (repeatable). Supported values: summary, description, fixed-issues, changes
      --sync-title                    Refresh the pull request title using fotingo's derived title rules
      --template-description string   Override the synced Description section content; expands escaped \n, \r\n, and \t
      --template-summary string       Override the synced Summary section content
      --title string                  Override the pull request title during sync

Global Flags:
  -b, --branch string   Base branch override (default: auto-detect)
      --debug           Show diagnostic output (includes verbose)
      --json            Output results as JSON
      --no-color        Disable colored output
      --quiet           Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose         Show step-level progress output
  -y, --yes             Accept defaults without prompting
